      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(ui): scope usage requests by agent filter",
        "body": "Fixes #87132.\n\n## Summary\n- pass a single selected `agent:<id>` usage query through to `sessions.usage` as `agentId`\n- populate the Usage page agent filter from `agents.list` so non-main agents are selectable before their usage sessions are loaded\n- reload usage data when the applied query changes the server-side agent scope\n- retry without `agentId` and remember legacy compatibility when an older gateway rejects the field\n\n## Tests\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs ui/src/ui/controllers/usage.node.test.ts ui/src/ui/app-render-usage-tab.test.ts ui/src/ui/views/usage.test.ts --reporter=dot`\n- `pnpm check:test-types`\n- `git diff --check`\n- `node scripts/run-oxlint.mjs --tsconfig config/tsconfig/oxlint.core.json ui/src/ui/app-render-usage-tab.ts ui/src/ui/controllers/usage.ts ui/src/ui/views/usage.ts ui/src/ui/views/usageTypes.ts ui/src/ui/app-render-usage-tab.test.ts ui/src/ui/controllers/usage.node.test.ts ui/src/ui/views/usage.test.ts`\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n**Behavior or issue addressed**: The Control UI Usage page rendered an agent filter but `loadUsage` always called `sessions.usage` without `agentId`, so the gateway scoped omitted requests to the default/main agent and non-main usage could not be loaded from that filter. This patch also preserves older-gateway compatibility by detecting and caching unsupported `agentId` rejection.\n\n**Real environment tested**: Local openclaw checkout at head `0a4a020cb32f64246b85b150a192cb3b38098cc2` on Linux with the repository UI controller and Usage view tests.\n\n**Exact steps or command run after this patch**: `HEAD=$(git rev-parse HEAD) node --import tsx -e 'import { resolveUsageAgentIdFromQuery, __test as testApi } from \"./ui/src/ui/controllers/usage.ts\"; const query = \"agent:research\"; console.log(`head=${process.env.HEAD}`); console.log(`${query} => ${resolveUsageAgentIdFromQuery(query) ?? \"<none>\"}`); console.log(`agent fallback detector => ${testApi.isLegacyUsageAgentUnsupportedError(new Error(\"invalid sessions.usage params: at root: unexpected property '''agentId'''\"))}`);'`\n\n**Evidence after fix**:\n```text\nhead=0a4a020cb32f64246b85b150a192cb3b38098cc2\nagent:research => research\nagent fallback detector => true\n```\n\n**Observed result after fix**: A single concrete `agent:research` Usage query resolves to `research`, which `loadUsage` includes as `agentId` in `sessions.usage` unless the gateway has been remembered as legacy-incompatible; the same controller detects an older gateway's `agentId` validation rejection and falls back to client-side filtering.\n\n**What was not tested**: I did not run a live browser against a multi-agent gateway; validation covered the UI controller request payload, legacy retry behavior, Usage tab reload behavior, and rendered agent filter options with local Vitest.\n",
